# PM2 Command Reference Guide

A complete list of useful PM2 commands with simple explanations.
Use this as your master reference for managing Node.js applications on a server.

---

## 1. Start Applications

### **Start a Node/Next.js App**

```
pm2 start app.js
pm2 start npm --name "myapp" -- start
```

**Use:** Starts an application using PM2.

### **Start App with a Custom Name**

```
pm2 start server.js --name project-backend
```

**Use:** Helps identify apps easily in the PM2 list.

---

## 2. Manage Running Apps

### **View All Running Processes**

```
pm2 list
```

### **View Logs**

```
pm2 logs
pm2 logs project-name
```

### **Restart App**

```
pm2 restart project-name
```

### **Stop App**

```
pm2 stop project-name
```

### **Delete App**

```
pm2 delete project-name
```

---

## 3. Auto-Restart on Server Boot (VERY Important)

### **Save Current PM2 Apps**

```
pm2 save
```

**Use:** Saves all running apps so PM2 can restore them after reboot.

### **Enable PM2 to Start on Boot**

```
pm2 startup systemd
```

**Use:** Generates a command that must be copied and run.
This registers PM2 with systemd so it runs automatically after reboot.

### **Run the Generated Command**

Example:

```
sudo env PATH=$PATH:/usr/bin pm2 startup systemd -u root --hp /root
```

---

## 4. Restore After Reboot

### **Auto-restore all saved apps**

```
pm2 resurrect
```

**Use:** Restores apps from the last `pm2 save`.

---

## 5. Monitor Performance

### **Live CPU & Memory Monitoring**

```
pm2 monit
```

### **App Info**

```
pm2 describe project-name
```

---

## 6. Log Controls

### **Clear All Logs**

```
pm2 flush
```

### **Clear Specific Logs**

```
pm2 flush project-name
```

---

## 7. Watch Mode (Auto Restart on File Change)

```
pm2 start app.js --watch
```

---

## 8. PM2 Backup File Locations

```
~/.pm2/dump.pm2     → Stores saved apps for resurrect
~/.pm2/logs/        → Contains logs
```

---

## 9. Full PM2 Reset (Use Only When Needed)

```
pm2 kill
pm2 delete all
pm2 reset all
```

**Use:** Clears PM2 completely.

---

# ⭐ Recommended Routine Commands

To make apps fully stable:

### After setting up all apps:

```
pm2 save
pm2 startup systemd
```

### After deploying updates:

```
pm2 restart app-name
pm2 save
```

---

**Keep this document safe — this is all you need to fully control PM2 on any server.**
